project.name: object_tracker
project.description:
This example uses an Object Tracking window to perform multi-object tracking (MOT). MOT is the process of accurately estimating the identity and position of multiple objects over time using a model that is based on incoming observations. The Object Tracking window couples trackers with detectors in a process called tracking-by-detection. Specifically, it uses an intersection-over-union (IOU) method of tracking-by-detection. In the tracking-by-detection method, an object detector is applied to each frame in a video. A tracker is then used to assign these detections to tracks. The IOU method tracks objects without using image information. Instead, it relies only on detection data. Using this method enables incremental and event-oriented tracking.
This example uses the following seven files:
The XML file (model.xml) associated with this example. det.txt is an input file. This file contains detection data. addObjId.csv is an output file. When you run the model, the object IDs are written to the addObjid.csv file. MOT17-04-FRCNN_1.csv is an input file. This file is the result of converting a video file into a CSV file. Each line in the CSV file represents a frame in the video. To obtain this file, download the object_tracker_xml.zip file from ftp://ftp.sas.com/techsup/download/esp/object_tracker_xml.zip and extract its contents. outputTracks.csv is an output file. When you run the model, the output tracks are written to the outputTracks.csv file. transpLong.csv is an output file. When you run the model, transposed output tracks are written to the transpLong.csv file. outputTracksLong.csv is an output file. When you run the model, output tracks in long format are written to the outputTracksLong.csv file.

window-source.name: swDetections
window-source.description: swDetections is a Source window. This is where detection data from the det.txt file enters the model.

window-compute.name: addObjId
window-compute.description: addObjId is a Compute window. This is where an object ID is assigned to each detection in the video file. A list of object IDs is written to the addObjId.csv file.

expr-initialize.initializer: integer last_frame; last_frame = 0; integer obj_number; obj_number = 0;

window-transpose.name: transpDetections
window-transpose.description: transpDetections is a Transpose window. This is where the detection data is transposed using each detectionâ€™s object ID.

window-aggregate.name: detAgg
window-aggregate.description: detAgg is an Aggregate window. This is where the detection data is aggregated.

window-source.name: swVideo
window-source.description: swVideo is a Source window. This is where data from the MOT17-04-FRCNN_1.csv file enters the model. This file is the result of converting a video file into a CSV file. Each line in the file represents one frame in the video.

window-join.name: getDetections
window-join.description: getDetections is a Join window. This is where the video frames from the MOT17-04-FRCNN_1.csv file and the detection data from the det.txt file are merged.

window-object-tracker.name: tracking
window-object-tracker.description: tracking is an Object Tracker window. This is where incoming detection data is used to perform multi-object tracking. This window uses an input schema to propose detections.

window-functional.name: outputTracks
window-functional.description: outputTracks is a Functional window. This is where the output tracks are written. A list of output tracks is written to the outputTracks.csv file.

window-transpose.name: transpLong
window-transpose.description: transpLong is Transpose window. This is where the output tracks are transposed and written to the transpLong.csv file.

window-filter.name: filterEmptyObjects
window-filter.description: filterEmptyObjects is a Filter window. This is where objects that do not contain any values are filtered out of the model.

window-functional.name: outputTracksLong
window-functional.description: outputTracksLong is a Functional window. This is where output tracks are written in long format to the outputTracksLong.csv file.
